Gold miner AngloGold Ashanti has appointed Rhidwaan Gasant lead independent director and Nelisiwe Magubane independent nonexecutive director. Gasant’s appointment is effective November 27 and Magubane’s January 1, 2020. Magubane, a former deputy director-general of the then Department of Minerals and Energy, also serves on the board of State power utility Eskom. She has extensive experience in the energy sector and is the founder of 70%-women-owned company Matleng Energy Solutions.